unit.doc: An absolute point in time, more efficient and precise than the float-based Time, but representing a narrower range of times.This module represents absolute times with nanosecond precision, approximately between the years 1823 and 2116 CE.

type.doc: ints are always immediate and so play nicely with the GC write barrier. Unfortunately, private int is necessary for the compiler to optimize uses.

module.doc: Similar to TimeSpanParts, but adding ns.
